ZCZC EE63
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 112300 UTC
SUNDAY EVENING THE AZORES HIGH 1028 COVERS THE S ATLANTIC WHILE A HEAT
LOW PERSISTS ACROSS THE IBERIAN PENINSULA THROUGHOUT THE FCST PERIOD. MEANWHILE
ANOTHER HIGH LIES OVER THE BENELUX 1027 WHILE A LOW PRESSURE LIES TO THE
S OF ICELAND 997 CREATING A COL REGION OVER SERN ENGLAND. THE LOW MOVS
SLWY EWARDS TOWARDS THE NORWEGIAN SEA WITH A TROUGH EXTENDING INTO THE N
SEA ON MONDAY ALLOWING THE AZORES HIGH TO BUILD ON ITS BACK-EDGE. THE RIDGE
CREATED THEN PIVOTS CLOCKWISE AND DECLINES OVER SERN ENGLAND ON TUESDAY AS
A DEEP LOW PRESSURE APPROACHES FM THE ATLANTIC. IT REACHES S BAILEY BY TUESDAY
MIDNIGHT 985 BEFORE CHANGING COURSE TOWARDS THE N WHILE WKN YET GENERATING
A CYCLONIC CIRCULATION ACROSS THE WHOLE OF THE BRITISH ISLES ON WEDNESDAY.
WHILE NO GALES ARE EXP TO AFFECT NITON THROUGH THIS PERIOD STRG WINDS MAY
DEVELOP ACROSS NW SHANNON TUESDAY AND WEDNESDAY AND ALSO TEMPO SE FITZROY
